description: India begins their Asia Cup 2025 campaign against UAE on September 10 in Dubai, followed by a highly anticipated match against Pakistan. Shubman Gill's return is set to boost the batting lineup, with Jitesh Sharma taking over as wicketkeeper. The team's bowling attack will be spearheaded by Jasprit Bumrah and Varun Chakravarthy.

description: Carlos Alcaraz clinched his second US Open title, defeating Jannik Sinner and securing a record $5 million prize. Despite the historic payout, US tax regulations will significantly reduce Alcaraz's earnings, potentially leaving him with around $2.5 million after federal and state taxes. A tax treaty with Spain offers some relief from double taxation.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Dinesh Karthik recalls MS Dhoni’s breakthrough during an ‘A’ series in Kenya, where his explosive power-hitting drew comparisons to Gary Sobers. With Rahul Dravid stepping back from wicketkeeping, Karthik briefly filled in before Dhoni took charge. “The lead role was always meant for him,” Karthik said, describing how Dhoni’s arrival quickly swept Indian cricket off its feet.
title: Nostalgia: DK calls Dhoni 'hero'; recalls comparisons with Sobers

author: TOI Education
description: The Staff Selection Commission (SSC) has cautioned candidates against sharing or discussing exam papers online, citing the Public Examinations Act, 2024. This law criminalizes unauthorized access and dissemination of exam content, with strict penalties including imprisonment and hefty fines. Aspirants, coaching centers, and digital platforms are urged to comply to maintain examination integrity.
title: SSC warning: Paper sharing, discussions barred under new Act; non-bailable offence

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The US–India Business Council urged both governments to resolve trade differences through respectful dialogue, emphasizing the strong US-India partnership amid global uncertainty. Hailing the recent positive remarks from President Trump and Prime Minister Modi, USIBC stressed the need for an ambitious trade deal to restore investor confidence and boost prosperity.
title: 'Too much at stake': USIBC lauds PM Modi, Trump's remarks; urges solving tariff row

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Abhinav Kashyap, director of 'Dabangg,' has reignited a long-standing feud by calling Salman Khan a 'gunda' and criticizing his family's influence in Bollywood. Kashyap, brother of Anurag Kashyap, transitioned from writing to directing, achieving fame with 'Dabangg' before a fallout over directing its sequel. He accuses the Khan family of sabotaging his career due to disagreements.
title: Who is Abhinav Kashyap? Meet Anurag Kashyap’s brother

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The trial of Ryan Routh, accused of attempting to assassinate Donald Trump, commenced chaotically in West Palm Beach. Routh, representing himself, faced Judge Aileen Cannon's reprimand for irrelevant jury selection questions. He cited witness unavailability, including a Costa Rica-based ex-colleague fearing arrest. Routh also voiced jail condition complaints, which were dismissed. Facing charges like attempted assassination and firearms violations, Routh pleaded not guilty.
title: Accused in Trump assassination attempt grills jurors with strange questions

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: In a groundbreaking development, University of Cambridge scientists have created a novel material poised to revolutionize arthritis treatment. This innovative substance, loaded with anti-inflammatory drugs, responds to pH changes indicative of flare-ups, releasing medication precisely when and where needed.
title: Arthritis: Scientists develop 'artificial cartilage' that releases drugs

author: JYOTIRMOY HALDER
description: Mishra, born in New Jersey to Indian parents, had already carved his place in history as the youngest-ever to earn the GM title at 12 years and four months. With this win, he set another record, becoming the youngest to defeat a reigning world champion in classical chess, eclipsing Gata Kamsky’s 1992 mark at 18, when he beat Garry Kasparov.
title: Big blow: D Gukesh's biggest defeat? How American GM aced the battle of youngest chess icons

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google is mandating its software engineers to exclusively use internal AI models for coding, driven by CEO Sundar Pichai's call for AI adoption to maintain competitiveness. Employees are expected to demonstrate AI proficiency, potentially influencing performance reviews and career advancement.
title: Google tightens AI use: Coders face strict rules; external tools prohibited

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Hardik Pandya grabbed attention at the Asia Cup training by wearing a Richard Mille RM 27-04 watch, estimated at Rs 20 crore. This rare timepiece, one of only 50 made in collaboration with Rafael Nadal, overshadows the tournament's prize money. Team India, led by Suryakumar Yadav, will begin their campaign on September 10.
title: Luxury overload: Rs 20 crore on the wrist; Pandya's watch worth more than Asia Cup prize money

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Rupert Murdoch's family has finalized a succession plan, ensuring Lachlan Murdoch's control over Fox Corp. until 2050. This arrangement, settling a dispute reminiscent of HBO's "Succession," grants Lachlan, along with his sisters Grace and Chloe, control of Fox News. Prudence MacLeod, Elisabeth Murdoch, and James Murdoch relinquished their claims for $3.
title: Rupert Murdoch succession battle: Eldest son Lachlan to control media empire

description: In Davalwadi village, Jalna, a farmer was arrested for allegedly strangling his 17-year-old daughter on September 5. The incident occurred because he disapproved of her relationship with a young man from their community. After the alleged murder, the father attempted to stage the scene to appear as a suicide by hanging her.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: The gut lining contains goblet cells which produce GAPs (goblet cell-associated antigen passages). The immune system receives training through GAPs, to identify and regulate gut bacteria. The reduction of mAChR4 by alcohol consumption prevents goblet cells from creating proper GAPs. Because of this, the immune system becomes less capable of handling gut bacteria because of this condition
title: Alcohol-linked liver disease: How gut bacteria damage the liver

The election was prompted by Jagdeep Dhankhar's resignation, and the new Vice President will serve as the Rajya Sabha's ex-officio Chairman.

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: A recent study reveals that human activities have pushed 60% of Earth's land outside the safe operating zone, threatening ecosystems. Deforestation, agriculture, and industrial expansion have disrupted carbon, water, and nitrogen cycles, particularly in Europe, Asia, and North America. Scientists urge immediate global action to protect natural systems and prevent irreversible damage to food security, water supplies, and the climate.

description: A security breach occurred in Mumbai's Navy Nagar. An unidentified man impersonating a naval officer stole an INSAS rifle. He also took two magazines with 40 live cartridges. description: Manoj Jarange, a quota activist, returned to his village after a hunger strike, warning the government to meet Maratha reservation demands by September 17. description: A gang of vehicle thieves, responsible for stealing over 40 motorcycles in Lucknow, were apprehended thanks to an unexpected intervention. description: Carlos Alcaraz secured his second US Open title in 2025, defeating Jannik Sinner in four sets and reclaiming the world No. 1 ranking. Alcaraz, now aiming for a Career Grand Slam, celebrated his best tournament performance.

description: The Philadelphia Eagles have acquired running back Tank Bigsby from the Jacksonville Jaguars just before Week 1 of the 2025 NFL season. description: Vivek Agnihotri's 'The Bengal Files' has released amidst controversy. The film clashed with 'Baaghi 4' and 'The Conjuring: Last Rites'. The cast includes Mithun Chakraborty, Anupam Kher and Pallavi Joshi.

description: In 2023, two-wheeler riders accounted for the highest share of road deaths in India, with 45% of fatalities. Accidents involving these vehicles also significantly impacted vulnerable road users, including pedestrians and cyclists.

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court has directed the Election Commission to accept Aadhaar cards as a valid proof of identity for voter list inclusion in Bihar, adding it as the 12th accepted document. This decision comes after the EC's initial resistance, with concerns raised about potential inclusion of illegal migrants.

author: TNN
description: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has ruled that apprehending armed militants qualifies as an "encounter" for reservation benefits for police personnel's children. Justice Jagmohan Bansal's order favored Sonam Kamboj, whose application was initially rejected because her father's service record did not meet the encounter participation criteria.

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Kajal Aggarwal, one of the most popular actresses in the South who has also made her mark in Bollywood, became the target of a shocking death hoax after reports claimed she had passed away in a road accident. The rumours spread rapidly on social media, forcing the actress to step in and put an end to the speculation.

author: TNN
description: Rohit Kumar, a daily wage labourer from Delhi, defies odds by excelling in marathons. Despite financial constraints after his medical studies in Russia were cut short, the 32-year-old has achieved podium finishes in multiple races, including a recent high-altitude marathon in Spiti.

author: VISHANT AGARWALA
description: Nepal revoked its social media ban following violent protests by Gen Z youths, resulting in multiple deaths and injuries, prompting the home minister's resignation. Opposition parties demand accountability for the state's actions, vowing continued protests despite the partial rollback. Demonstrations, fueled by corruption concerns and economic inequality, spread across the country, leading to curfews and army deployment in affected areas.
title: Social media ban in Nepal: Govt restores Facebook, X; Gen Z protests to continue
